1775
02:00:31,308 --> 02:00:35,460
<i>I remember I had this feeling I would be</i>
<i>killed right outside the jail.</i>

1776
02:00:35,748 --> 02:00:39,024
<i>I knew Paulie was still pissed at me</i>
<i>and he's such a hothead.</i>

1777
02:00:39,108 --> 02:00:40,826
<i>And I was worried about Jimmy.</i>

1778
02:00:40,908 --> 02:00:45,220
<i>See, Jimmy knew if Paulie found out</i>
<i>he was in the drug deals with me...</i>

1779
02:00:45,628 --> 02:00:48,825
<i>... Paulie would have Jimmy whacked</i>
<i>even before me.</i>

1780
02:00:50,028 --> 02:00:51,825
<i>This is the bad time.</i>

1781
02:00:52,748 --> 02:00:55,262
<i>I didn't feel safe until I got home.</i>

1782
02:00:56,508 --> 02:01:00,217
<i>Now my plan was to stay alive</i>
<i>long enough to sell off the dope...</i>

1783
02:01:00,428 --> 02:01:04,740
<i>... the cops never found, then disappear</i>
<i>until things got straightened out.</i>

1784
02:01:06,508 --> 02:01:09,068
Fuck! Where's the stuff I left, Karen?

1785
02:01:09,348 --> 02:01:11,225
I flushed it down the toilet.

1786
02:01:12,428 --> 02:01:13,338
What?

1787
02:01:14,348 --> 02:01:16,384
What was I supposed to do?

1788
02:01:16,908 --> 02:01:20,537
That was worth $60,000!
I need that money! That's all we got!

1789
02:01:21,028 --> 02:01:23,064
They had a search warrant!

1790
02:01:23,748 --> 02:01:28,060
That's all the money we had! I was
depending on that! Why did you do that?

1791
02:01:28,268 --> 02:01:30,828
I had to! They were going to find it!

1792
02:01:31,068 --> 02:01:34,663
- They wouldn't have found it!
- They would have! I swear!

1793
02:01:35,748 --> 02:01:37,659
They would've found it!

1794
02:01:39,388 --> 02:01:40,867
Why did you do that?

1795
02:01:41,308 --> 02:01:44,425
- They would have found it.
- Why did you do that?

1796
02:01:45,828 --> 02:01:47,181
Oh, my God!

1797
02:01:47,788 --> 02:01:49,938
- I had to do it.
- Oh, my God!

1798
02:02:25,188 --> 02:02:27,179
<i>Paulie, I'm really sorry.</i>

1799
02:02:29,628 --> 02:02:32,665
I don't know what else to say.
I know I fucked up.

1800
02:02:32,908 --> 02:02:34,341
Yeah, you fucked up.

1801
02:02:37,708 --> 02:02:39,539
But I'm all right now.

1802
02:02:41,148 --> 02:02:44,663
I can be trusted now. I'm clean.
On my kids, I'm clean.

1803
02:02:45,348 --> 02:02:47,782
You looked in my eyes and lied to me.

1804
02:02:48,708 --> 02:02:52,587
You treated me like a fucking jerk.
Like I was never nothing to you.

1805
02:02:52,828 --> 02:02:55,547
After what you said,
I couldn't come to you.

1806
02:02:56,748 --> 02:02:58,704
You know, I was ashamed.

1807
02:03:01,868 --> 02:03:03,460
I'm ashamed now.

1808
02:03:06,988 --> 02:03:09,183
But I got nowhere else to go.

1809
02:03:12,268 --> 02:03:16,500
You're all I got. And I really,
really need your help. I really do.

1810
02:03:22,188 --> 02:03:23,257
Take this.

1811
02:03:37,708 --> 02:03:40,097
And now I've got to turn my back on you.

1812
02:03:49,788 --> 02:03:51,460
<i>Thirty-two hundred bucks.</i>

1813
02:03:51,868 --> 02:03:54,860
<i>That's what he gave me.</i>
<i>$3,200 for a lifetime.</i>

1814
02:03:56,428 --> 02:03:58,988
<i>It wasn't even enough to pay for the coffin.</i>

1815
02:03:59,068 --> 02:04:01,377
- <i>We got to get out.</i>
- <i>I don't want to run.</i>

1816
02:04:01,468 --> 02:04:05,097
Am I supposed to pick up
and leave everything? Go hiding?

1817
02:04:05,628 --> 02:04:07,584
I don't want to do that.

1818
02:04:08,028 --> 02:04:11,782
If we stay around here we're dead.
You got it? We' re dead.

1819
02:04:13,468 --> 02:04:17,984
They're right. You took too much
of that stuff. You're totally paranoid.

1820
02:04:21,228 --> 02:04:22,741
How's he doing?

1821
02:04:23,268 --> 02:04:24,496
He's okay.

1822
02:04:25,068 --> 02:04:26,660
They sobered him up.

1823
02:04:26,908 --> 02:04:28,819
Good. Glad to hear it.

1824
02:04:32,908 --> 02:04:36,025
- What kind of questions they been asking?
- I don't know.

1825
02:04:37,668 --> 02:04:41,104
I got my mind on so many other things.
I got no money.

1826
02:04:41,628 --> 02:04:44,301
The girls are old enough
to read the newspapers.

1827
02:04:44,388 --> 02:04:46,265
Tell him he's got to call me.

1828
02:04:46,988 --> 02:04:50,617
As soon as you talk to him,
he's got to call me. It's important.

1829
02:04:50,828 --> 02:04:54,184
He doesn't know I came here to see you.
It's like he's crazy.

1830
02:04:54,468 --> 02:04:57,380
- Take this. It's a couple thousand.
- Thanks, Jimmy.

1831
02:04:57,548 --> 02:04:59,778
Don't worry, everything will be all right.

1832
02:04:59,868 --> 02:05:02,905
I got some beautiful Dior dresses.
You want to have them?

1833
02:05:02,988 --> 02:05:04,819
Pick out a few for yourself.

1834
02:05:05,628 --> 02:05:07,539
- For my mom.
- Yeah, whatever.

1835
02:05:07,788 --> 02:05:10,097
Not here. In the store on the corner.

1836
02:05:10,348 --> 02:05:12,816
It's swag, so I got it down on the corner.

1837
02:05:18,468 --> 02:05:20,299
Go ahead, sweetheart, I'll see you.

1838
02:05:20,388 --> 02:05:21,867
- Thanks.
- Don't worry.

1839
02:05:22,108 --> 02:05:24,383
- I'll try.
- He's got to call me.

1840
02:05:27,108 --> 02:05:28,177
Over here?

1841
02:05:28,348 --> 02:05:29,701
Right down there.

1842
02:05:43,708 --> 02:05:45,664
It's over there, on the corner.

1843
02:05:45,948 --> 02:05:47,097
Right there.

1844
02:06:19,468 --> 02:06:21,823
No! Go ahead! It's right there!

1845
02:06:22,108 --> 02:06:24,178
No, Jimmy! I'm in a hurry!

1846
02:06:24,428 --> 02:06:27,147
My mom's watching the kids!
I got to get home!

1847
02:06:27,388 --> 02:06:29,060
I'll come back later!

1848
02:06:56,188 --> 02:06:57,541
What happened?

1849
02:06:58,348 --> 02:06:59,576
Nothing.

1850
02:06:59,948 --> 02:07:02,382
- What happened?
- I just got scared.

1851
02:07:05,148 --> 02:07:06,581
Got the keys?

1852
02:07:07,868 --> 02:07:09,062
What happened?

1853
02:07:09,228 --> 02:07:11,458
I just got scared. It's okay.

1854
02:07:11,628 --> 02:07:13,027
Are you all right?

1855
02:07:19,708 --> 02:07:23,621
<i>If you're part of a crew nobody ever</i>
<i>tells you they're going to kill you.</i>

1856
02:07:24,508 --> 02:07:26,260
<i>It doesn't happen that way.</i>

1857
02:07:26,508 --> 02:07:29,705
<i>There aren't any arguments</i>
<i>or curses like in the movies.</i>

1858
02:07:29,948 --> 02:07:33,623
<i>Your murderers come with smiles.</i>
<i>They come as your friends.</i>

1859
02:07:34,028 --> 02:07:36,098
<i>People who cared for you all your life.</i>

1860
02:07:36,188 --> 02:07:40,659
<i>They always seem to come when you're</i>
<i>weakest and most in need of their help.</i>

1861
02:07:40,908 --> 02:07:43,866
<i>So I met Jimmy in a crowded place</i>
<i>we both knew.</i>

1862
02:07:44,108 --> 02:07:47,703
<i>I got there 15 minutes early</i>
<i>and Jimmy was already there.</i>

1863
02:07:48,348 --> 02:07:52,739
<i>He took the booth near the window</i>
<i>so he could see everyone who drove up.</i>

1864
02:07:53,068 --> 02:07:55,377
<i>He wanted to make sure I wasn't tailed.</i>

1865
02:07:55,628 --> 02:07:58,426
<i>He was jumpy. He hadn't touched a thing.</i>

1866
02:07:59,308 --> 02:08:02,266
<i>On the surface,</i>
<i>everything was supposed to be fine.</i>

1867
02:08:02,508 --> 02:08:04,817
<i>We were supposed to be discussing</i>
<i>my case.</i>

1868
02:08:04,908 --> 02:08:09,538
<i>But I had a feeling Jimmy was trying</i>
<i>to sense if I'd rat on him to save my neck.</i>

1869
02:08:11,068 --> 02:08:14,583
I been telling you your whole life,
don't talk on the phone.

1870
02:08:14,828 --> 02:08:16,341
Now you understand?

1871
02:08:18,988 --> 02:08:22,458
It's going to be okay.
You got a good chance to beat this case.

1872
02:08:25,388 --> 02:08:29,540
Well, you know that kid from the city
we were talking about? You know?

1873
02:08:32,028 --> 02:08:36,465
The kid turned out to be a rat. As soon
as he got pinched, he ratted on everybody.

1874
02:08:38,348 --> 02:08:40,942
I know where he is. He's hiding out.

1875
02:08:42,028 --> 02:08:43,541
Know what I'm saying?

1876
02:08:48,188 --> 02:08:51,703
Would you have a problem going
with Anthony to take care of that?

1877
02:08:54,188 --> 02:08:55,701
No, not at all.

1878
02:08:56,988 --> 02:08:58,706
That way they got nothing.

1879
02:09:07,068 --> 02:09:09,946
<i>Jimmy had never asked me</i>
<i>to whack somebody before.</i>

1880
02:09:10,188 --> 02:09:14,181
<i>But now he's asking me to go to Florida</i>
<i>and do a hit with Anthony.</i>

1881
02:09:20,828 --> 02:09:24,741
<i>That's when I knew I would never</i>
<i>have come back from Florida alive.</i>

1882
02:09:37,308 --> 02:09:40,664
Wherever you move me,
I asked once and I'll tell you again...

1883
02:09:40,828 --> 02:09:43,058
...I don't want to go any place cold.

1884
02:09:43,868 --> 02:09:45,620
You don't have a choice.

1885
02:09:46,348 --> 02:09:49,101
Come on. Whoever fucking controls it...

1886
02:09:49,548 --> 02:09:51,937
...just no place cold. Do that for me.

1887
02:09:52,188 --> 02:09:54,179
He's bronchial, that's why.

1888
02:09:54,428 --> 02:09:56,817
If he's bronchial we'll consider that.

1889
02:09:56,988 --> 02:09:58,819
I'd like to go someplace not cold.

1890
02:09:58,908 --> 02:10:02,218
Can I ask you some questions?
What about my parents?

1891
02:10:03,668 --> 02:10:04,737
What about them?

1892
02:10:04,828 --> 02:10:08,104
Am I going to see them?
Am I going to talk to them?

1893
02:10:08,348 --> 02:10:10,862
Don't I have some kind of contact
with them?

1894
02:10:11,228 --> 02:10:12,183
No.

1895
02:10:13,308 --> 02:10:16,664
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
You mean to tell me...

1896
02:10:16,908 --> 02:10:20,901
...if something happens to my parents
and they get sick, I can't see them?

1897
02:10:20,988 --> 02:10:23,866
Maybe something can be worked out
if they're sick.

1898
02:10:24,108 --> 02:10:26,668
If there's extraordinary circumstances...

1899
02:10:26,908 --> 02:10:29,706
I can't do this. I can't do this, Henry.

1900
02:10:30,348 --> 02:10:32,339
I can't leave my parents.

1901
02:10:33,628 --> 02:10:35,619
Karen, I told you before.

1902
02:10:36,508 --> 02:10:39,898
I'm not going to do this unless
you and the kids come with me.

1903
02:10:41,548 --> 02:10:43,539
I can't do it without you.

1904
02:10:43,788 --> 02:10:46,302
So you do whatever, but... that's it.

1905
02:10:48,988 --> 02:10:51,548
- You need Henry, not me, right?
- That's right.

1906
02:10:51,788 --> 02:10:53,858
I don't care whether you go or not.

1907
02:10:54,428 --> 02:10:57,704
If it'll make him a better witness,
I want you with him.

1908
02:10:57,948 --> 02:10:59,461
They don't want me.

1909
02:10:59,548 --> 02:11:03,063
Henry'll be in the protection program.
They can't get to him.

1910
02:11:03,388 --> 02:11:06,585
They can only get to him
by getting to you or your kids.

1911
02:11:06,748 --> 02:11:09,308
If he goes into the program
you're in danger.

1912
02:11:09,468 --> 02:11:11,698
- I don't know anything.
- Don't give me...

1913
02:11:11,788 --> 02:11:13,301
...the babe-in-the-woods routine.

1914
02:11:13,388 --> 02:11:17,540
I've listened to those wiretaps
and I've heard you talk about cocaine.

1915
02:11:17,788 --> 02:11:21,542
Conversation after conversation
you talked to Henry on the phone.

1916
02:11:25,948 --> 02:11:28,587
It doesn't matter.
Whether he goes to jail...

1917
02:11:28,748 --> 02:11:31,387
...or stays on the streets, he's a dead man.

1918
02:11:31,948 --> 02:11:33,779
He knows it and you know it.

1919
02:11:35,068 --> 02:11:37,343
What about the kids and school?

1920
02:11:37,788 --> 02:11:39,301
I mean, what goes on?

1921
02:11:40,028 --> 02:11:42,019
Go to Wall Street and get real crooks.

1922
02:11:42,108 --> 02:11:44,417
Whoever sold you those suits
had a sense of humor.

1923
02:11:44,508 --> 02:11:47,784
What it comes down to is
we're your only salvation.

1924
02:11:48,188 --> 02:11:51,863
We'll save your life, his life,
and we'll keep you out of jail.

1925
02:11:54,988 --> 02:11:57,946
This morning you told the jury
about your background.

1926
02:11:58,028 --> 02:12:00,337
<i>It was easy for us to disappear.</i>

1927
02:12:00,588 --> 02:12:04,740
<i>My house was in my mother-in-law's name.</i>
<i>My cars were registered to my wife.</i>

1928
02:12:04,908 --> 02:12:08,184
<i>My Social Security cards</i>
<i>and driver's licenses were phonies.</i>

1929
02:12:08,428 --> 02:12:10,578
<i>I never voted or paid taxes.</i>

1930
02:12:11,068 --> 02:12:15,300
<i>My birth certificate and arrest sheet</i>
<i>were all that showed I was alive.</i>

1931
02:12:15,468 --> 02:12:18,028
- Do you see him here in this courtroom?
- Yes.

1932
02:12:18,348 --> 02:12:21,146
Will you please point him out for the jury?

1933
02:12:23,148 --> 02:12:27,539
Let the record show that Mr. Hill
identified the defendant, James Conway.

1934
02:12:29,148 --> 02:12:31,537
Do you also know a man
named Paul Cicero?

1935
02:12:31,788 --> 02:12:34,018
- Do you see him in the courtroom?
- Yes.

1936
02:12:34,268 --> 02:12:36,657
Can you point him out for the jury?

1937
02:12:37,468 --> 02:12:41,541
Let the record show Mr. Hill
identified the defendant Paul Cicero.

1938
02:12:43,308 --> 02:12:44,900
I have a document...

1939
02:12:45,148 --> 02:12:47,821
<i>The hardest thing was leaving the life.</i>

1940
02:12:48,348 --> 02:12:49,986
<i>I still loved the life.</i>

1941
02:12:50,108 --> 02:12:53,896
<i>We were treated like movie stars</i>
<i>with muscle. We had it all.</i>

1942
02:12:54,428 --> 02:12:57,465
<i>Our wives, mothers, kids,</i>
<i>everybody rode along.</i>

1943
02:12:57,868 --> 02:13:01,144
<i>I had paper bags filled with jewelry</i>
<i>stashed in the kitchen.</i>

1944
02:13:01,228 --> 02:13:03,298
<i>I had a bowl of coke next to my bed.</i>

1945
02:13:03,388 --> 02:13:07,063
People call them rats because
they will do anything to survive.

1946
02:13:07,228 --> 02:13:09,059
- Objection!
- Objection sustained.

1947
02:13:09,148 --> 02:13:12,902
- I know nothing about being a rat.
- You know everything about it!

1948
02:13:14,588 --> 02:13:16,897
<i>Anything I wanted was a phone call away.</i>

1949
02:13:16,988 --> 02:13:20,264
<i>Free cars. Keys to a dozen hideouts</i>
<i>all over the city.</i>

1950
02:13:20,508 --> 02:13:22,942
<i>I'd bet 20 grand over a weekend...</i>

1951
02:13:23,148 --> 02:13:27,061
<i>... then blow the winnings in a week</i>
<i>or go to sharks to pay the bookies.</i>

1952
02:13:27,308 --> 02:13:28,661
Didn't matter.

1953
02:13:28,988 --> 02:13:33,140
It didn't mean anything. When I was broke
I would go rob some more.

1954
02:13:33,948 --> 02:13:35,620
We ran everything.

1955
02:13:35,948 --> 02:13:39,623
We paid off cops. We paid off lawyers.
We paid off judges.

1956
02:13:40,188 --> 02:13:43,976
Everybody had their hands out.
Everything was for the taking.

1957
02:13:45,468 --> 02:13:47,106
And now it's all over.

1958
02:13:47,708 --> 02:13:49,664
<i>That's the hardest part.</i>

1959
02:13:50,428 --> 02:13:52,180
<i>Today everything is different.</i>

1960
02:13:52,268 --> 02:13:56,022
<i>There's no action. I have to wait around</i>
<i>like everyone else.</i>

1961
02:13:56,508 --> 02:13:58,499
<i>Can't even get decent food.</i>

1962
02:13:58,748 --> 02:14:01,979
<i>After I got here I ordered spaghetti</i>
<i>with marinara sauce...</i>

1963
02:14:02,108 --> 02:14:04,338
<i>... and I got egg noodles and ketchup.</i>

1964
02:14:04,428 --> 02:14:06,259
<i>I'm an average nobody.</i>

1965
02:14:07,148 --> 02:14:10,026
<i>I get to live the rest of my life</i>
<i>like a schnook.</i>

1966
02:15:27,548 --> 02:15:29,504
Subtitles : Filou ;-)

